# Dev Server Rule

The user runs the Expo dev server in a persistent Cursor terminal. The agent NEVER starts or kills it directly.

## Normal flow (no restart needed)
Editing `.js` / `.ts` / `.tsx` files → **Fast Refresh handles it automatically**. Just save; the app updates within seconds.

## When a restart IS required
Tell the user to stop the server (`Ctrl+C`) and rerun the start command when any of these happen:

| Trigger | Restart command |
|---|---|
| New npm/expo package installed | `npx expo start --tunnel --clear` |
| `app.json` / `app.config.js` changed | `npx expo start --tunnel` |
| New native module added | `npx expo start --tunnel --clear` |
| Metro stuck / bundle error won't clear | `npx expo start --tunnel --clear` |

## What the agent must NOT do
- Run `npx expo start` from the agent shell
- Kill or `Stop-Process` Metro/node processes
- Use `netstat` to hunt for port conflicts

## How the agent should communicate restarts
After installing a package or making a change that needs a reload, always say:

> "Stop your terminal server (`Ctrl+C`) and restart with:
> ```
> npx expo start --tunnel --clear
> ```
> Then scan the QR code again in Expo Go."

## User's dev server setup
- App lives in `bryce-app/`
- Normal start: `cd bryce-app && npx expo start --tunnel`
- After package installs: add `--clear` flag
- Web preview appears at the localhost URL shown in the terminal
